main event: A white balloon-shaped object was observed moving with air currents and sudden jerks in Fallon, Nevada on 9/10/68 - 9/15Z.
interesting points: The object was observed through a 15x35 telescope for 20 to 30 minutes.
The report indicates that the evidence presented suggests the object was not a balloon, contrary to the initial conclusion.
The document includes forms and diagrams related to the sighting, such as a compass rose and an observer sketch.
The sighting was reported to the Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation.
Multiple witnesses, including a retired dairy farmer, observed the phenomenon.
witnesses: civilian, including a retired dairy farmer
